      "has_lesson_plan": true,
      "relative_position": 31,
      "properties": {
        "assessment": true,
        "overview": "**What story or message do I want to convey about my data?**\n\nFor this project, students use the skills they have developed throughout this unit to analyze data from a text file and create a visual representation for a topic they are interested in or meaningful to them. Students use the data they chose in a previous lesson to identify the patterns and message they want to convey visually using The Theater. After brainstorming and planning, students develop their programs.",
        "preparation": "* Print copies of the Abstract Data Art Project Planning Guide (one for each student)",
        "student_overview": "**What story or message do I want to convey about my data?**\n\nFor this project, you use the skills you have developed throughout this unit to analyze data from a text file and create a visual representation for a topic you are interested in or that is meaningful to you. You use the data you chose in a previous lesson to identify the patterns and message you want to convey visually using The Theater. After brainstorming and planning, you develop your program."
