    {
      "key": "Personal Narrative Project",
      "name": "Personal Narrative Project",
      "absolute_position": 32,
      "lockable": false,
      "has_lesson_plan": true,
      "relative_position": 32,
      "properties": {
        "assessment": true,
        "overview": "**What personal experiences or interests do I want to portray in a collage or animation using images and filters?**\n\nFor this project, students use the skills they have developed throughout this unit to create new image filters or develop image manipulation algorithms to use in a collage or animation that portrays personal experiences and/or interests using The Theater. Students choose the topic for their personal narrative and the image filters or manipulation techniques they want to use. After brainstorming and planning, students develop their programs to create their personal narrative collage or animation.",
        "preparation": "* Print copies of the Personal Narrative Project Planning Guide (one for each student)",
        "student_overview": "**What personal experiences or interests do I want to portray in a collage or animation using images and filters?**\n\nFor this project, you use the skills you have developed throughout this unit to create new image filters or develop image manipulation algorithms to use in a collage or animation that portrays personal experiences and/or interests using The Theater. You choose the topic for your personal narrative and the image filters or manipulation techniques you want to use. After brainstorming and planning, you develop your program to create your personal narrative collage or animation."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "lesson.key": "Personal Narrative Project",
        "lesson_group.key": "lessonGroup-2",
        "script.name": "csa4-alt-2025"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "Natural Language Processing Project",
      "name": "Natural Language Processing Project",
      "absolute_position": 33,
      "lockable": false,
      "has_lesson_plan": true,
      "relative_position": 33,
      "properties": {
        "assessment": true,
        "overview": "**How will I use natural language processing techniques to analyze, manipulate, or generate text in a program?**\n\nFor this project, students use the skills they have developed throughout this unit to create a program that uses natural language processing techniques to analyze, manipulate, and/or generate text. Students choose how they will implement basic natural language processing techniques to understand text and respond accordingly. After brainstorming and planning, students develop their programs.",
        "preparation": "* Print copies of the Natural Language Processing Project Planning Guide (one for each student)",
        "student_overview": "**How will I use natural language processing techniques to analyze, manipulate, or generate text in a program?**\n\nFor this project, you use the skills you have developed throughout this unit to create a program that uses natural language processing techniques to analyze, manipulate, and/or generate text. You choose how you will implement basic natural language processing techniques to understand text and respond accordingly. After brainstorming and planning, you develop your program."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "lesson.key": "Natural Language Processing Project",
        "lesson_group.key": "lessonGroup-2",
        "script.name": "csa4-alt-2025"
