    {
      "key": "042cfb8c-c0c1-4218-9daa-3f8850d56252",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "The `Integer` and `Double` classes have methods to work with integer and decimal values. Let's take a look at some of their methods and capabilities.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Wrapper Class Methods",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "042cfb8c-c0c1-4218-9daa-3f8850d56252",
        "lesson_activity.key": "cd1316c0-5444-40ff-a880-f2d9c1bdf7a4"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "4305a309-d920-4ac3-b1cb-1d3858f85b58",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to introduce the `Integer` class and its methods.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to introduce the `Double` class and its methods.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to demonstrate the `Integer` and `Double` constructors.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Show the video – *Wrapper Classes - Part 2*.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Videos are used throughout the curriculum to spark discussions, supplement key concepts with additional explanations and examples, and expose students to the various roles and backgrounds of individuals in computer science.\n\nWhile interacting with the video, turn on closed captioning so students can also read along as they watch.\n\nTo encourage active engagement and reflection, use one or more of the strategies discussed in the [**Guide to Curriculum Videos**](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FqIUpJg6MrgdtbFGLobSojOz0u1m5Jge1nMAjUqI5ZM/edit?usp=sharing)."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "4305a309-d920-4ac3-b1cb-1d3858f85b58",
        "lesson_activity.key": "cd1316c0-5444-40ff-a880-f2d9c1bdf7a4"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "01b0652c-d27a-47d1-a74a-9f012c6ef574",
      "position": 11,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to define ***parsing*** and demonstrate the example."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "01b0652c-d27a-47d1-a74a-9f012c6ef574",
        "lesson_activity.key": "cd1316c0-5444-40ff-a880-f2d9c1bdf7a4"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f4f85353-5a5a-4f9d-863c-2f87ca52e56d",
      "position": 12,
      "properties": {
        "description": "When you were exploring the program, you might have noticed something interesting that happens when you add one to the maximum value for an integer or subtract one from the minimum value for an integer.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f4f85353-5a5a-4f9d-863c-2f87ca52e56d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "cd1316c0-5444-40ff-a880-f2d9c1bdf7a4"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "0ae1c896-43b7-421f-afa0-1e55403896ed",
      "position": 13,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What did you notice about the maximum and minimum values for an `int`?*\n* *What happens when you add or subtract one from the maximum or minimum values?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share the maximum and minimum values and their findings from adding to the maximum value or subtracting from the minimum value.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Retrieve-Pair-Share strategy to facilitate this discussion by directing students to write down their thoughts and ideas first, then pair up students to compare their answers and expand their notes. This allows time for individual processing and idea generation before sharing thoughts with others. Ask students to share the ideas they discussed with their partners as a class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "0ae1c896-43b7-421f-afa0-1e55403896ed",
        "lesson_activity.key": "cd1316c0-5444-40ff-a880-f2d9c1bdf7a4"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a99c0db0-4f04-471a-bf0c-8643b83befc1",
      "position": 14,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Do This:** Explain the minimum and maximum values for integers:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Integers in Java have 32 bits of space\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `Integer.MIN_VALUE`\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `Integer.MAX_VALUE`\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to define ***overflow***.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to define ***underflow***."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a99c0db0-4f04-471a-bf0c-8643b83befc1",
        "lesson_activity.key": "cd1316c0-5444-40ff-a880-f2d9c1bdf7a4"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b0c593bf-344c-4694-9423-e2debcf85518",
      "position": 15,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Representing integer and decimal values as objects are useful for specific scenarios. When represented as objects, we can use the methods in the `Integer` and `Double` classes to work with these values.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Using Wrapper Classes",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b0c593bf-344c-4694-9423-e2debcf85518",
        "lesson_activity.key": "cd1316c0-5444-40ff-a880-f2d9c1bdf7a4"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d6b64a52-6871-4b18-b7d7-0555ac441617",
      "position": 16,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to define ***autoboxing*** and explain that autoboxing also occurs when a primitive value is passed as a parameter to a method that expects an object of the corresponding wrapper class.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to define ***unboxing*** and explain that unboxing occurs when a wrapper class object is passed as a parameter to a method that expects a value of the corresponding primitive type.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 5 on Code Studio to complete Levels 5, 6, and 7. Students complete a Check for Understanding, then continue to complete a choice level on Level 6 to practice using the `Integer` class. On Level 7, students complete a choice level to practice using the `Double` class.",
        "progression_name": "Practice: Wrapper Classes",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Check for Understanding is an AP-style multiple choice question that can be used as a formative assessment to gauge understanding of using the `Integer` and `Double` classes.\n\nThe practice level can be used as a formative assessment to gauge understanding of using the `Integer` and `Double` classes."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d6b64a52-6871-4b18-b7d7-0555ac441617",
        "lesson_activity.key": "cd1316c0-5444-40ff-a880-f2d9c1bdf7a4"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d7268888-9817-470b-8652-25296a2bf9b7",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a sticky note or scrap piece of paper.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students respond to the prompt on the sticky note or scrap piece of paper.",
        "name": "But, Because, So",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time permits, have students share their responses with a neighbor."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d7268888-9817-470b-8652-25296a2bf9b7",
        "lesson_activity.key": "0c5e4471-3923-476e-97ba-5ebfa9146d3a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d26ba871-1536-4484-9c42-b634ba9d20de",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the concepts covered in this lesson.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "The Unit 6 Guide includes the Question of the Day and an end-of-lesson reflection prompt for students to summarize what they have learned and reflect on their progress. Have students respond to these prompts after reviewing the concepts covered in this lesson to help them process and make meaningful connections with the new content."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
