    {
      "key": "756051fb-a562-4d96-a5ad-84ca63e714c4",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *How do we get an individual element from an array?*\n* *How can we do this with an `ArrayList` based on what we know about its structure?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students recall accessing the array element by referring to the index number. Students guess that the `ArrayList` class has methods they can use to access an element.",
        "name": "Accessing Elements",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Retrieve-Pair-Share strategy to facilitate this discussion by directing students to write down their thoughts and ideas first, then pair up students to compare their answers and expand their notes. This allows time for individual processing and idea generation before sharing thoughts with others. Ask students to share the ideas they discussed with their partners as a class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "756051fb-a562-4d96-a5ad-84ca63e714c4",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9a34ca2f-18d1-4dd7-9aea-045727a990f6"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a9b180d2-254a-4169-952a-aa42f39b326f",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Introduction"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a9b180d2-254a-4169-952a-aa42f39b326f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "85bbd2ce-a2ac-46cd-8911-c1009aafd16a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "22c03e69-10bd-41db-b034-57e8ecc4c9df",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "An `ArrayList` has methods that can change the state of an `ArrayList`. Today, we'll explore other useful methods for working with the data stored in an `ArrayList`.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "22c03e69-10bd-41db-b034-57e8ecc4c9df",
        "lesson_activity.key": "85bbd2ce-a2ac-46cd-8911-c1009aafd16a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "8c71d7eb-99da-4980-ac52-a9b1f16f1e64",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to predict the program's outcome, then run the program to compare their predictions to the actual outcome.",
        "progression_name": "Predict and Run: Manipulating Elements"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "8c71d7eb-99da-4980-ac52-a9b1f16f1e64",
        "lesson_activity.key": "85bbd2ce-a2ac-46cd-8911-c1009aafd16a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7ad95f9a-abc3-4f54-a958-f39b88b07546",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What did you notice about the code in this program?*\n* *What do you wonder about the code in this program?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students notice that the `get()` method retrieves items from the `ArrayList` and the `set()` method sets the value at a specific index to a specified value Students also notice that both methods are similar to indexing arrays because they retrieve a value or assign a new value at a specified index. Students may wonder if there is a method to change an element to a new value or how they might use these methods inside of a loop to obtain or change multiple elements."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7ad95f9a-abc3-4f54-a958-f39b88b07546",
        "lesson_activity.key": "85bbd2ce-a2ac-46cd-8911-c1009aafd16a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "df5b3768-e533-4654-ae0e-f12f03e2f597",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Like 1D and 2D arrays, we can access elements in an `ArrayList` by referring to their index position. We can use methods in the `ArrayList` class to retrieve and modify elements.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Exploring ArrayList Methods",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "df5b3768-e533-4654-ae0e-f12f03e2f597",
        "lesson_activity.key": "85bbd2ce-a2ac-46cd-8911-c1009aafd16a"
      }
    },
