    {
      "key": "de421b2c-09bf-4bfb-bd8f-354f72f612f0",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We have previously seen how we can use methods in the `ArrayList` class to add elements and get the number of elements in the list. The `ArrayList` class also has methods to retrieve and modify elements.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "ArrayList Methods",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "de421b2c-09bf-4bfb-bd8f-354f72f612f0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "85bbd2ce-a2ac-46cd-8911-c1009aafd16a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e0f17ec9-3cba-4010-a77b-25aa74b22985",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to demonstrate the `get()` method.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to demonstrate the `set()` method.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Step through each line of code with students and discuss the updates to the `ArrayList` after each command.\n\nIf students are struggling to understand the methods, explain that `ArrayList`s use `get()` and `set()` methods instead of using the square brackets `array[index]` that arrays use because `ArrayList` is a class with methods that provide access to its array instance variable."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e0f17ec9-3cba-4010-a77b-25aa74b22985",
        "lesson_activity.key": "85bbd2ce-a2ac-46cd-8911-c1009aafd16a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "23584545-3787-4f96-b418-36af448e7907",
      "position": 11,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We can traverse an `ArrayList` similar to how we traverse a 1D array. We can use either a `for` or a `while` loop and use the loop control variable to refer to the index of a value in the list. Let's take a look at how a `for` loop can be used to access each element in an `ArrayList`.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "23584545-3787-4f96-b418-36af448e7907",
        "lesson_activity.key": "85bbd2ce-a2ac-46cd-8911-c1009aafd16a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a71700e3-e6bf-42b9-b60d-9299775edc9e",
      "position": 12,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to demonstrate traversing an `ArrayList` and review the `IndexOutofBoundsException`."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a71700e3-e6bf-42b9-b60d-9299775edc9e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "85bbd2ce-a2ac-46cd-8911-c1009aafd16a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f0167d69-90a8-4f49-8bb8-115eda788551",
      "position": 13,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Now that we know how to use methods in the `ArrayList` class to add, retrieve, and modify elements, we can use the same algorithms we wrote to work with 1D arrays to find and manipulate elements in an `ArrayList`.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Manipulating Elements",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f0167d69-90a8-4f49-8bb8-115eda788551",
        "lesson_activity.key": "85bbd2ce-a2ac-46cd-8911-c1009aafd16a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3ead09ff-3c8a-44ac-b0f9-6f4e253e1f4a",
      "position": 14,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 5 on Code Studio to complete Levels 5, 6, and 7. Students complete a Check for Understanding, then continue to Level 6 to complete a choice level to practice using the `get()` and `set()` methods. On Level 7, students complete a choice level to traverse an `ArrayList` to find or manipulate its elements.",
        "progression_name": "Practice: Manipulating Elements",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Check for Understanding is an AP-style multiple choice question that can be used as a formative assessment to gauge understanding of traversing `ArrayList`s.\n\nThe practice level can be used as a formative assessment to gauge understanding of traversing `ArrayList`s."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3ead09ff-3c8a-44ac-b0f9-6f4e253e1f4a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "85bbd2ce-a2ac-46cd-8911-c1009aafd16a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c487c035-b43a-4ee2-8936-1e5fa4a5daf5",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "When we're working with text and larger amounts of data, we might want to use an `ArrayList` to store and work with this information. For our Natural Language Processing Project, we could use an `ArrayList` to store and process this information.",
        "name": "Using ArrayLists",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c487c035-b43a-4ee2-8936-1e5fa4a5daf5",
        "lesson_activity.key": "17c1e56d-ff2f-4cdd-86e8-a8ebb3563bee"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e4553dbe-1317-4bb8-b525-262e47d4b15e",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *How might we use an `ArrayList` to store and process information in our projects?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students will likely have several different ideas for using an `ArrayList`, such as to store words from a sentence or to add phrases or information that their program learns to a list.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Hold That Thought strategy to allow students to write down their thoughts on paper first. Emphasize that they do not need to write complete sentences – they can write a few words, bullet points, draw a quick sketch, or anything else that will help them gather and recall their thoughts when it is time to share with the class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e4553dbe-1317-4bb8-b525-262e47d4b15e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "17c1e56d-ff2f-4cdd-86e8-a8ebb3563bee"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "cb645255-01f3-44be-a610-6eef22276765",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the concepts covered in this lesson.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "The Unit 6 Guide includes the Question of the Day and an end-of-lesson reflection prompt for students to summarize what they have learned and reflect on their progress. Have students respond to these prompts after reviewing the concepts covered in this lesson to help them process and make meaningful connections with the new content."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "cb645255-01f3-44be-a610-6eef22276765",
        "lesson_activity.key": "17c1e56d-ff2f-4cdd-86e8-a8ebb3563bee"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "66d16c09-9c55-4fbd-aefe-8d1286b6ac03",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "---"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "66d16c09-9c55-4fbd-aefe-8d1286b6ac03",
