    {
      "key": "a0a94c2a-15bc-4c2c-bb93-16b056757880",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "*Check For Understanding Question(s) and solutions can be found in each lesson on Code Studio. These questions can be used for an exit ticket.*",
        "name": "Assessment: Check for Understanding",
        "progression_name": "Check for Understanding"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a0a94c2a-15bc-4c2c-bb93-16b056757880",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1e9420d3-c1f2-475d-b42f-f0374d50caa3"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3a1a23eb-e640-4a27-943e-e09216d42f64",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "When we traversed a 2D array in row-major order, we were able to find information about data contained in each row or about all of the values in the 2D array. Sometimes, we may want to find information about data contained in each column.",
        "name": "Solve the Problem",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3a1a23eb-e640-4a27-943e-e09216d42f64",
        "lesson_activity.key": "53815fb8-7a4b-49c0-aee6-da344cd0a4dd"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "485ed63c-bb0c-475c-90e3-a6ddffe28e71",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Based on what we know about Java and 2D arrays, how could we find the sum of the values in each column in this 2D array?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students suggest various solutions to this problem, including going through the 2D array column-by-column instead of row-by-row or keeping track of which column they are in.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Retrieve-Pair-Share strategy to facilitate this discussion by directing students to write down their thoughts and ideas first, then pair up students to compare their answers and expand their notes. This allows time for individual processing and idea generation before sharing thoughts with others. Ask students to share the ideas they discussed with their partners as a class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "485ed63c-bb0c-475c-90e3-a6ddffe28e71",
        "lesson_activity.key": "53815fb8-7a4b-49c0-aee6-da344cd0a4dd"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "4e63f8fc-b258-40a6-ae3e-74fa1bd3771a",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Introduction"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "4e63f8fc-b258-40a6-ae3e-74fa1bd3771a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "023be62a-00d6-4ce0-88e0-4072f4869e06"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "be19f489-b044-4a01-b92c-883a99c12acd",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "In the previous lesson, we learned how to traverse a 2D array in row-major order. We can also traverse a 2D array in column-major order.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "be19f489-b044-4a01-b92c-883a99c12acd",
        "lesson_activity.key": "023be62a-00d6-4ce0-88e0-4072f4869e06"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2f3dd5de-60e1-4167-ba5c-b66a773c04ca",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to predict the program's outcome, then run the program to compare their predictions to the actual outcome.",
        "progression_name": "Predict and Run: Column-Major Traversal"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2f3dd5de-60e1-4167-ba5c-b66a773c04ca",
        "lesson_activity.key": "023be62a-00d6-4ce0-88e0-4072f4869e06"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "65afd7d0-8865-4cc5-a198-96f69a48a7aa",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What did you notice about the code in this program?*\n* *What do you wonder about the code in this program?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students notice the outer loop traverses each column, and the inner loop traverses each row. Students also notice that the syntax for accessing an individual element is still the same. Students may wonder when they would traverse a 2D array in column-major order."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "65afd7d0-8865-4cc5-a198-96f69a48a7aa",
        "lesson_activity.key": "023be62a-00d6-4ce0-88e0-4072f4869e06"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "6778615f-9e99-4203-bde4-8d7dc3d78b73",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Sometimes we may want to traverse a 2D array column-by-column rather than row-by-row. When we go through a 2D array column-by-column, this is called a column-major traversal.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Column-Major Traversal",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "6778615f-9e99-4203-bde4-8d7dc3d78b73",
        "lesson_activity.key": "023be62a-00d6-4ce0-88e0-4072f4869e06"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "656c3300-3680-4e10-bf45-d9e54c7e8ba1",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Show the video – *Column-Major Traversal*.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Videos are used throughout the curriculum to spark discussions, supplement key concepts with additional explanations and examples, and expose students to the various roles and backgrounds of individuals in computer science.\n\nWhile interacting with the video, turn on closed captioning so students can also read along as they watch.\n\nTo encourage active engagement and reflection, use one or more of the strategies discussed in the [**Guide to Curriculum Videos**](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FqIUpJg6MrgdtbFGLobSojOz0u1m5Jge1nMAjUqI5ZM/edit?usp=sharing)."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "656c3300-3680-4e10-bf45-d9e54c7e8ba1",
        "lesson_activity.key": "023be62a-00d6-4ce0-88e0-4072f4869e06"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "4e0022c4-c85f-4fff-9edc-147315c89557",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to demonstrate a column-major traversal.\n\n**Group:** Place students in pairs.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of the Tracing Column-Major Traversals handout.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students complete the Tracing Column-Major Traversals handout.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "You can choose to model completing the first few rows of the trace table as a class first, then have students work with their partners to complete the remaining rows."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "4e0022c4-c85f-4fff-9edc-147315c89557",
        "lesson_activity.key": "023be62a-00d6-4ce0-88e0-4072f4869e06"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c59321f5-53a6-486f-bdaf-749265ba37f9",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Traversing a 2D array column-by-column allows us to answer different types of questions. We can use this approach to find the sum of values in each column or to see if a column contains specific information.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Traversing 2D Arrays",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c59321f5-53a6-486f-bdaf-749265ba37f9",
        "lesson_activity.key": "023be62a-00d6-4ce0-88e0-4072f4869e06"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e21cc583-2edd-4788-83cc-a5ac4c9d9d98",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 2 on Code Studio to complete Levels 2, 3, and 4. Students complete a Check for Understanding on Level 2, then continue to Level 3 to complete a choice level to traverse a 2D array in column-major order. On Level 4, students complete a choice level to apply a standard 1D array algorithm to a 2D array using the console or The Theater.",
        "progression_name": "Practice: Column-Major Traversal",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Check for Understanding is an AP-style multiple choice question that can be used as a formative assessment to gauge understanding of traversing a 2D array in column-major order.\n\nThe practice levels can be used as a formative assessment to gauge understanding of writing nested loops to traverse a 2D array in column-major order."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e21cc583-2edd-4788-83cc-a5ac4c9d9d98",
        "lesson_activity.key": "023be62a-00d6-4ce0-88e0-4072f4869e06"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f1486f50-c63b-42ae-a6b0-4c0c61a86503",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We can traverse a 2D array in row-major order or column-major order depending on how we want to access the information. Both approaches have several similarities and differences.",
        "name": "Row-Major vs Column-Major",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f1486f50-c63b-42ae-a6b0-4c0c61a86503",
        "lesson_activity.key": "c4ce2647-ba86-42f5-a3d3-9157ad3760c3"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "51c994e7-b13f-4b8b-83b9-7bbadc1b90c5",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What are the differences between the row-major and column-major order traversal algorithms?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students note that the `for` loop headers are swapped. In row-major order, the loop variable in the outer `for` loop is used as a row index, and the loop variable from the inner `for` loop is used as a column index. Conversely, in column-major order, the loop variable in the outer `for` loop is used as a column index, and the loop variable from the inner `for` loop is used as a row index.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to explain use cases for each traversal approach.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the concepts covered in this lesson.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "The Unit 5 Guide includes the Question of the Day and an end-of-lesson reflection prompt for students to summarize what they have learned and reflect on their progress. Have students respond to these prompts after reviewing the concepts covered in this lesson to help them process and make meaningful connections with the new content."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "51c994e7-b13f-4b8b-83b9-7bbadc1b90c5",
        "lesson_activity.key": "c4ce2647-ba86-42f5-a3d3-9157ad3760c3"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "710ad882-8299-4e10-bb44-ceefc7a8e260",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Key Vocabulary"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "710ad882-8299-4e10-bb44-ceefc7a8e260",
        "lesson_activity.key": "c4ce2647-ba86-42f5-a3d3-9157ad3760c3"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "917ec928-de2e-4317-834a-d368dd98181f",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "---"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
