      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e5697cb8-9d84-4388-91cf-6886ff744732",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What did you notice about the code in this program?*\n* *What do you wonder about the code in this program?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students notice that the color of each pixel is modified by calculating new values for the red, green, and blue values. Students may wonder about other ways they can manipulate colors or make connections to image filters they might have seen in other apps and programs."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e5697cb8-9d84-4388-91cf-6886ff744732",
        "lesson_activity.key": "85de2e63-128a-4d9f-9412-32f401731c1a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "76b5aedc-d300-4f75-9422-22b0107cc626",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to explain how grayscale images are created.\n\n**Group:** Place students in pairs.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each pair a copy of the Modifying Colors handout.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students write pseudocode for an algorithm to create an image filter or effect.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Planning the Algorithm",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Remind students about how they implemented standard algorithms to find the average of values in a 1D array. Ask students to consider how this algorithm would be modified to create the grayscale effect."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "76b5aedc-d300-4f75-9422-22b0107cc626",
        "lesson_activity.key": "85de2e63-128a-4d9f-9412-32f401731c1a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "93d363f8-6b67-4174-855a-733411d9c6db",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students compare their algorithms with another group and make revisions as needed."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "93d363f8-6b67-4174-855a-733411d9c6db",
        "lesson_activity.key": "85de2e63-128a-4d9f-9412-32f401731c1a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "9fca3bd7-5d2e-46b5-b107-e73921cf870d",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Let's implement our algorithms to create a new image filter! We can also use and modify other standard algorithms to create additional image filters and effects.",
        "name": "Creating Image Filters",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "9fca3bd7-5d2e-46b5-b107-e73921cf870d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "85de2e63-128a-4d9f-9412-32f401731c1a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b229b766-6c56-4b22-81c8-f5564da3265b",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 2 on Code Studio to complete Levels 2 through 5. Students complete a Check for Understanding, then continue to Level 3 to implement their algorithm. On Levels 4 and 5, students complete a choice level to create an image filter.",
        "progression_name": "Practice: Image Filters",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Check for Understanding is an AP-style multiple choice question that can be used as a formative assessment to gauge understanding of traversing and manipulating a 2D array.\n\nThe practice level can be used as a formative assessment to gauge understanding of traversing and manipulating a 2D array."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b229b766-6c56-4b22-81c8-f5564da3265b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "85de2e63-128a-4d9f-9412-32f401731c1a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c7975367-c23c-44b8-af74-064591ae7f57",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "You have made a lot of progress in developing your software engineering skills. We have seen how these skills are useful to solve a variety of problems and create programs like what we have used in our daily lives.",
        "name": "Software Engineering Skills",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c7975367-c23c-44b8-af74-064591ae7f57",
        "lesson_activity.key": "436ba58e-4f1d-47e4-8b7f-df67be974c57"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "fcbfde1c-8270-4ab8-b107-a44cff3eacea",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *How has your perception of software engineering changed in this unit?*\n* *How have your software engineering skills improved in this unit?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share how their perception of software engineering has changed, including how computer science influences different industries and decisions. Students identify the software engineering skills and characteristics they feel they improved in this unit.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the concepts covered in this lesson.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "The Unit 5 Guide includes the Question of the Day and an end-of-lesson reflection prompt for students to summarize what they have learned and reflect on their progress. Have students respond to these prompts after reviewing the concepts covered in this lesson to help them process and make meaningful connections with the new content."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "fcbfde1c-8270-4ab8-b107-a44cff3eacea",
        "lesson_activity.key": "436ba58e-4f1d-47e4-8b7f-df67be974c57"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "31a51f3c-9154-4472-bbd1-cfdb851874f8",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "---"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "31a51f3c-9154-4472-bbd1-cfdb851874f8",
        "lesson_activity.key": "436ba58e-4f1d-47e4-8b7f-df67be974c57"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "124074bb-14f7-4c1a-9f6a-e1232deb3bdd",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "*Check For Understanding Question(s) and solutions can be found in each lesson on Code Studio. These questions can be used for an exit ticket.*",
        "name": "Assessment: Check for Understanding",
        "progression_name": "Check for Understanding"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "124074bb-14f7-4c1a-9f6a-e1232deb3bdd",
        "lesson_activity.key": "436ba58e-4f1d-47e4-8b7f-df67be974c57"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "251701a5-aa44-4801-b00e-2a4d5173893c",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Demonstrate the activity by acting as the magician.\n1. Ask students to choose a card.\n2. Shuffle the cards.\n3. Reveal a card and ask if that was the card. Add one to the number of guesses.\n4. Put the revealed card into a pile of checked cards until the next round.\n5. Repeat steps 2 through 4 until the revealed card is the one the student chose.",
        "name": "World's Worst Magician",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Repeat the process several times to create a variety in the number of guesses it took to find the chosen card."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "251701a5-aa44-4801-b00e-2a4d5173893c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "26cf23f4-13de-4364-a93e-0108324725d5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a5db0ff2-13e2-4ff8-a0f0-1802387c27e7",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *Am I the world’s worst magician?*\n* *How many guesses would the world’s best magician take?*\n* *How many guesses would the real world’s worst magician take?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students suggest that the world's best magician always finds the correct card on the first try. Students share that the world’s worst magician would guess the correct card on their very last attempt.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Retrieve-Pair-Share strategy to facilitate this discussion by directing students to write down their thoughts and ideas first, then pair up students to compare their answers and expand their notes. This allows time for individual processing and idea generation before sharing thoughts with others. Ask students to share the ideas they discussed with their partners as a class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a5db0ff2-13e2-4ff8-a0f0-1802387c27e7",
        "lesson_activity.key": "26cf23f4-13de-4364-a93e-0108324725d5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "8f7af04e-5248-40dc-953b-aada0c588dec",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Linear Search"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "8f7af04e-5248-40dc-953b-aada0c588dec",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ed79da49-1b4e-4356-a56e-4ee0b3dc0d0c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a03d03fd-1fb4-455b-9e60-ca7caab423e6",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "When we have written algorithms to find a target value in a data structure, we are searching the entire data structure one element at a time from first to last. This approach is actually one of many standard algorithms used by software engineers for searching a data structure.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a03d03fd-1fb4-455b-9e60-ca7caab423e6",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ed79da49-1b4e-4356-a56e-4ee0b3dc0d0c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ef45c4ff-0cda-4e2d-9be9-e8347068f142",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to complete Levels 1, 2, and 3. Students investigate the program, make changes to the program as prompted, and observe the results.",
        "progression_name": "Investigate and Modify: Linear Search"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ef45c4ff-0cda-4e2d-9be9-e8347068f142",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ed79da49-1b4e-4356-a56e-4ee0b3dc0d0c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "19f8521a-e20d-4cba-98d5-57b4b5b620ae",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What do you notice about the code in this program?*\n* *What do you wonder about the code in this program?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students notice the method traverses each array one element at a time from first to last. Students also notice that the program displays each element it checks and keeps a count of how many checks it executes. Students may wonder if there is a faster way to search for data.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to define ***linear/sequential search*** and demonstrate using the algorithm with a 1D array.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to demonstrate using the algorithm with a 2D array.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to define the ***best case***, ***average case***, and ***worst case***.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What is the best case for the World's Worst Magician?*\n* *What is the average case for the World's Worst Magician?*\n* *What is the worst case for the World's Worst Magician?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students identify the best case as guessing the card on the first try, and the worst case as the total number of cards. Students suggest values for the average case based on their experience in the warm up activity.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Retrieve-Pair-Share strategy to facilitate this discussion by directing students to write down their thoughts and ideas first, then pair up students to compare their answers and expand their notes. This allows time for individual processing and idea generation before sharing thoughts with others. Ask students to share the ideas they discussed with their partners as a class.\n\nTo help students identify the average case, ask students additional guiding questions. For example:\n* *What does finding the average of a scenario like this consist of?*\n* *How many times should we test the algorithm to identify the average case?*"
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "19f8521a-e20d-4cba-98d5-57b4b5b620ae",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ed79da49-1b4e-4356-a56e-4ee0b3dc0d0c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "543253f0-3323-4274-adbc-61d0443fd522",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "When we need to choose an algorithm for a specific task, we typically choose or create the most efficient one. Software engineers use different techniques and tools to measure the efficiency of algorithms. One way that we can measure efficiency is by counting the number of times a code segment executes.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Counting Executions with Code",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "543253f0-3323-4274-adbc-61d0443fd522",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ed79da49-1b4e-4356-a56e-4ee0b3dc0d0c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "080984f8-d636-42b4-81b2-3976223204e9",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to define ***execution count***.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of the Counting Executions with Code handout.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students complete the Counting Executions with Code handout.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students compare their findings with a partner."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "080984f8-d636-42b4-81b2-3976223204e9",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ed79da49-1b4e-4356-a56e-4ee0b3dc0d0c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "677ae6b5-2317-460a-8369-52875a018767",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "As software engineers, one of our primary goals is to develop software that provides usefulness and value to users. Our goal for the Creative Coding with the Console Project is to create a program using the console that portrays a personal interest or solves a problem. When we develop programs to convey a personal interest, we typically have an audience in mind that we want to show our work to. When we develop programs to solve a problem, we typically have a specific type of user that we want to benefit from the program.",
        "name": "User Stories",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "677ae6b5-2317-460a-8369-52875a018767",
        "lesson_activity.key": "753b85af-a39a-46d3-8de9-f5d41a4f061d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "9dd5b361-eb9e-49ec-85da-7079c872669d",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to review user stories.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students write user stories for their project on page five of their Creative Coding with the Console Project Planning Guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the concepts covered in this lesson.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "The Unit 8 Guide includes the Question of the Day and an end-of-lesson reflection prompt for students to summarize what they have learned and reflect on their progress. Have students respond to these prompts after reviewing the concepts covered in this lesson to help them process and make meaningful connections with the new content."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "9dd5b361-eb9e-49ec-85da-7079c872669d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "753b85af-a39a-46d3-8de9-f5d41a4f061d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a28addfd-25b6-48a8-9efc-5fe174f31f99",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Key Vocabulary"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a28addfd-25b6-48a8-9efc-5fe174f31f99",
        "lesson_activity.key": "753b85af-a39a-46d3-8de9-f5d41a4f061d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7ca97952-7ea7-4bb0-af6d-f35d8aa7c605",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "---"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7ca97952-7ea7-4bb0-af6d-f35d8aa7c605",
