    {
      "key": "ef4d240a-0935-43a7-be8e-e2ac5b85bd59",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "*Check For Understanding Question(s) and solutions can be found in each lesson on Code Studio. These questions can be used for an exit ticket.*",
        "name": "Assessment: Check for Understanding",
        "progression_name": "Check for Understanding"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ef4d240a-0935-43a7-be8e-e2ac5b85bd59",
        "lesson_activity.key": "753b85af-a39a-46d3-8de9-f5d41a4f061d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "eac562dc-b9ce-4cab-ab7a-35075fa4984d",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Software engineers often have to solve sorting problems in addition to searching problems. Just like there are many standard algorithms for searching, there are also standard algorithms for sorting data.",
        "name": "Sorting Data",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "eac562dc-b9ce-4cab-ab7a-35075fa4984d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "628c9bb5-0b15-47d4-ba6f-bf1d50d74a72"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f1c7a6ce-ed99-40df-a7a9-9346e85f6455",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *How do you use the \"Sort By\" feature on an e-commerce site like Amazon? What are some of the different options offered to sort the products?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students note that they use the \"Sort By\" feature to find products quickly. Students share that they can sort by size, color, weight, delivery time, price, and other options.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *How do you think websites like Amazon perform these sorts?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students suggest algorithms for sorting products, such as comparing pairs of values and performing swaps until they are in the correct order.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Retrieve-Pair-Share strategy to facilitate this discussion by directing students to write down their thoughts and ideas first, then pair up students to compare their answers and expand their notes. This allows time for individual processing and idea generation before sharing thoughts with others. Ask students to share the ideas they discussed with their partners as a class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f1c7a6ce-ed99-40df-a7a9-9346e85f6455",
        "lesson_activity.key": "628c9bb5-0b15-47d4-ba6f-bf1d50d74a72"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "50b7fa69-f312-4411-8bf4-bf947926243d",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day.",
        "name": "Introduction"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "50b7fa69-f312-4411-8bf4-bf947926243d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "78bfa3eb-71e0-40f4-8131-3d30ac5ee7fe"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e9ee235b-aeab-420f-828b-29a329a1cb1e",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "In previous lessons, you have learned how to implement different search algorithms. We can only use a linear search for an unsorted list, while a sorted list could utilize a more optimized search algorithm like binary search.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e9ee235b-aeab-420f-828b-29a329a1cb1e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "78bfa3eb-71e0-40f4-8131-3d30ac5ee7fe"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3e297309-ba55-42b9-b717-357d49694720",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to complete Levels 1, 2, and 3. Students investigate the program, make changes to the program as prompted, and observe the results.",
        "progression_name": "Investigate and Modify: Selection Sort"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3e297309-ba55-42b9-b717-357d49694720",
        "lesson_activity.key": "78bfa3eb-71e0-40f4-8131-3d30ac5ee7fe"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "324d9777-d994-42c3-9e52-27263805869c",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What do you notice about the code in this program?*\n* *What do you wonder about the code in this program?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students notice that the selection sort combines standard algorithms they have used to find the minimum value and to swap elements to place the values in the correct order. Students also notice that the program displays each element it checks and keeps a count of how many checks it executes. Students may wonder if there are faster ways to sort the data."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "324d9777-d994-42c3-9e52-27263805869c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "78bfa3eb-71e0-40f4-8131-3d30ac5ee7fe"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "6ef3d2ca-4986-4c37-b478-40fb946a7546",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "This program uses an algorithm that software engineers often use to sort elements in a list. Let's take a closer look at how this algorithm works.",
        "duration": "20",
        "name": "Selection Sort",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "6ef3d2ca-4986-4c37-b478-40fb946a7546",
        "lesson_activity.key": "78bfa3eb-71e0-40f4-8131-3d30ac5ee7fe"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d1f076e3-1d38-4310-a986-91a1b33f1c4e",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Do This:** Click through the animated slides to define ***selection sort*** and demonstrate the example:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> First swap\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Second swap\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Third swap\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Final check\n\n**Group:** Place students in groups of four to six.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each group a copy of the Selection Sort handout and five cups.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the instructions for the Selection Sort activity.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students complete the Selection Sort handout.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If groups finish early with sorting their cups, combine groups to use selection sort on a larger number of cups to analyze the efficiency."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d1f076e3-1d38-4310-a986-91a1b33f1c4e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "78bfa3eb-71e0-40f4-8131-3d30ac5ee7fe"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "26a64891-069e-4e29-a9d5-7d6b2a272744",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students compare their findings with a partner.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to demonstrate the pseudocode for the selection sort algorithm."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "26a64891-069e-4e29-a9d5-7d6b2a272744",
        "lesson_activity.key": "78bfa3eb-71e0-40f4-8131-3d30ac5ee7fe"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "edcc9b27-cadc-4bcf-a3b1-150f3adb1993",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "The selection sort algorithm is useful for sorting data in our programs, but there are benefits and limitations to this approach to sorting.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "edcc9b27-cadc-4bcf-a3b1-150f3adb1993",
        "lesson_activity.key": "78bfa3eb-71e0-40f4-8131-3d30ac5ee7fe"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "577bf759-2ebf-4e82-a163-7d9c16d2833e",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *When would the selection sort algorithm be useful in our programs?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students realize that larger lists might make this approach less efficient and suggest using the selection sort algorithm to sort small sets of data.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Retrieve-Pair-Share strategy to facilitate this discussion by directing students to write down their thoughts and ideas first, then pair up students to compare their answers and expand their notes. This allows time for individual processing and idea generation before sharing thoughts with others. Ask students to share the ideas they discussed with their partners as a class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "577bf759-2ebf-4e82-a163-7d9c16d2833e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "78bfa3eb-71e0-40f4-8131-3d30ac5ee7fe"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "8c440a72-a470-4f1a-9cb3-5d42a1c00143",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What are some limitations or issues with using the selection sort algorithm?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students identify limitations to the selection sort, such as that the size of the list impacts the efficiency of the algorithm."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "8c440a72-a470-4f1a-9cb3-5d42a1c00143",
        "lesson_activity.key": "78bfa3eb-71e0-40f4-8131-3d30ac5ee7fe"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b55b9217-c698-4c26-975f-9370dbec214f",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We just learned a lot of new information today, which may have even answered some of the Need to Know questions you wrote down about the Creative Coding Project. As we progress through the unit, it is helpful to stop and note what we have learned that is related to or useful for the project.",
        "name": "Revisiting the Need to Knows",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b55b9217-c698-4c26-975f-9370dbec214f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e57c714d-fccd-476e-a764-c758e3d5cbd8"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "dd072ee8-46aa-4068-a3bd-8a2bb7163ecf",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students review the questions they wrote in the \"Need to Know\" column on page two of their Creative Coding with the Console Project Planning Guide. Students add new questions to this column, check off any answered questions, and write answers to any questions in the \"Learned\" column.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students share what they added to their chart with a partner.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time permits, you can also have students share as a class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "dd072ee8-46aa-4068-a3bd-8a2bb7163ecf",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e57c714d-fccd-476e-a764-c758e3d5cbd8"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "18c6fac2-ef99-4066-9fc3-48e6754e6494",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the concepts covered in this lesson.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "The Unit 8 Guide includes the Question of the Day and an end-of-lesson reflection prompt for students to summarize what they have learned and reflect on their progress. Have students respond to these prompts after reviewing the concepts covered in this lesson to help them process and make meaningful connections with the new content."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "18c6fac2-ef99-4066-9fc3-48e6754e6494",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e57c714d-fccd-476e-a764-c758e3d5cbd8"
      }
    },
