    {
      "key": "91e48141-da0c-4b11-be1f-87ee32d1f8dd",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student several sticky notes.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students participate in a Gallery Walk to view each other's programs and leave sticky notes noting what they like about the program."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "91e48141-da0c-4b11-be1f-87ee32d1f8dd",
        "lesson_activity.key": "184fbaee-f509-4044-b00e-dc3ed2e4f5ac"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7129237a-d1db-4b64-bcba-c6603335ea2f",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to respond to the End of Project Reflection prompt on the Personal Narrative Project Planning Guide.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Wrap Up",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time permits, have students share their thoughts and ideas with a neighbor."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7129237a-d1db-4b64-bcba-c6603335ea2f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "184fbaee-f509-4044-b00e-dc3ed2e4f5ac"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e16eed3a-1a01-4bbb-a57f-83e130f2d929",
      "position": 11,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students complete a short end-of-unit survey. Although their answers are anonymous, the aggregated data will be available to you once at least five students have completed the survey.",
        "name": "End of Unit Survey",
        "progression_name": "End of Unit Survey",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "We also have a teacher end-of-unit survey to learn more about how the unit went for you and your students. While students take their survey, please complete [**this end of unit survey for teachers**](https://studio.code.org/form/teacher_end_of_unit_survey?survey_data%5Bunit_number%5D=5) as well. Your feedback is valued and appreciated!"
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e16eed3a-1a01-4bbb-a57f-83e130f2d929",
        "lesson_activity.key": "184fbaee-f509-4044-b00e-dc3ed2e4f5ac"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "1b607925-cf59-4926-93b0-d0b13ed04ae1",
      "position": 12,
      "properties": {
        "description": "---"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "1b607925-cf59-4926-93b0-d0b13ed04ae1",
        "lesson_activity.key": "184fbaee-f509-4044-b00e-dc3ed2e4f5ac"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "57ff0333-b6fe-4105-89d7-35f32c7cd079",
      "position": 13,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Personal Narrative Project:** Use the rubric in the Personal Narrative Project Planning Guide to assess the projects.",
        "name": "Assessment: Grading the Project"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "57ff0333-b6fe-4105-89d7-35f32c7cd079",
        "lesson_activity.key": "184fbaee-f509-4044-b00e-dc3ed2e4f5ac"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "eeb06f43-27bc-44b4-ab7a-2887c782da93",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "The unit assessment project assesses proficiency in the knowledge and skills developed in this unit. It is completed in three class periods to plan and create the program, including choosing a topic or goal and implementing an algorithm. Students participate in planning and feedback activities to solve problems, reinforce software development practices and self-image as software engineers, and improve their programs.\n\nIf there is not enough time for the three-day project, a one-day option achieves the targeted learning objectives and goals. If using this option, refer to the [**Natural Language Processing Project 1-Day Lesson Plan**](https://levelbuilder-studio.code.org/s/csa6-2023/lessons/14). While the one-day option covers the learning objectives and goals, it shortens planning and reflection time. Consider this tradeoff when deciding which version to use."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "eeb06f43-27bc-44b4-ab7a-2887c782da93",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f8ec16ba-5f20-446a-b3c4-b6ab142f02f7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b4bd7a11-57fa-4a5e-8922-94ad9623690b",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We have seen some examples of programs that use natural language processing techniques throughout the unit. Programs and devices often use natural language processing to interact with a user to answer questions, find information, or execute commands.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Warm Up",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b4bd7a11-57fa-4a5e-8922-94ad9623690b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9b07d017-a5af-4866-b08a-03627cad04dd"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3e88592e-ce1a-431d-9bc9-06af4c294ba6",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Show examples of different types of programs and devices that use natural language processing.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What does this make you wonder about how you could create a program that uses natural language processing to analyze, manipulate, or generate text?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share ideas about programs they might make using natural language processing, such as chatbots, story generators, or social media analyzers."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3e88592e-ce1a-431d-9bc9-06af4c294ba6",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9b07d017-a5af-4866-b08a-03627cad04dd"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "eb1b4fac-f6f2-448b-a145-658b5c3f3e82",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Over the next few days, you will be developing a program that uses natural language processing techniques to analyze, manipulate, or generate text.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Brainstorming and Planning",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "eb1b4fac-f6f2-448b-a145-658b5c3f3e82",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9b07d017-a5af-4866-b08a-03627cad04dd"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e9f8e6d8-7739-4b25-85e2-f981055ade07",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of the Natural Language Processing Project Planning Guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the project requirements.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to read the rubric on pages 2 and 3.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What do you notice about the project requirements and rubric? What does success look like for this project?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share what they notice about the project requirements and rubric and identify the components to implement in their program.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What barriers do you anticipate to achieving success on this project?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students identify barriers they anticipate and share any questions they have about the project.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Hold That Thought strategy to allow students to write down their thoughts on paper first. Emphasize that they do not need to write complete sentences – they can write a few words, bullet points, draw a quick sketch, or anything else that will help them gather and recall their thoughts when it is time to share with the class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e9f8e6d8-7739-4b25-85e2-f981055ade07",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9b07d017-a5af-4866-b08a-03627cad04dd"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "366ed47a-3865-42f7-b8c9-5f98c10e2b83",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Do This:** Introduce the steps students will take each day to complete the project:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Day 1 steps\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Day 2 steps\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Day 3 steps"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "366ed47a-3865-42f7-b8c9-5f98c10e2b83",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9b07d017-a5af-4866-b08a-03627cad04dd"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a11e8403-8939-4869-baa6-92d5e4fe86ca",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Before you begin writing your program, you first need to decide how you will use natural language processing techniques in your program. You will need to plan how you will organize your program and interact with a user, and identify the algorithms you need to develop to analyze text.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a11e8403-8939-4869-baa6-92d5e4fe86ca",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9b07d017-a5af-4866-b08a-03627cad04dd"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "852fe2d7-fa1f-4698-8233-7f8400110c9b",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to brainstorm the program they will create, create UML diagrams for their classes, and identify the algorithms they need to develop on the Natural Language Processing Project Planning Guide."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "852fe2d7-fa1f-4698-8233-7f8400110c9b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9b07d017-a5af-4866-b08a-03627cad04dd"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3054398c-85a8-4ae2-a2d8-e0c09277b859",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to develop their Natural Language Processing Good Project.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Development",
        "progression_name": "Natural Language Processing Project"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3054398c-85a8-4ae2-a2d8-e0c09277b859",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9b07d017-a5af-4866-b08a-03627cad04dd"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "29d0e842-c7a9-4b74-8c43-1450f65f4420",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "This is a good time to commit our code and save our new superclass and subclasses to the Backpack. Anytime we make changes to our programs, it is helpful to commit, or save, our work as a new version in case we need to revert to a previous version.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "29d0e842-c7a9-4b74-8c43-1450f65f4420",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9b07d017-a5af-4866-b08a-03627cad04dd"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "07a648d3-04c4-449a-8b15-e8e6f3dc9897",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Play the music clip to cue committing their code and saving their classes to the Backpack.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Using music to cue transitions helps create routines in the classroom. When students hear cues, they know it is time to transition to a specific activity. Emphasize to students what the music clip means, and be consistent with the use of the music clip to cue the activity.\n\nClick the blue play icon on the slide to play the music cue."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "07a648d3-04c4-449a-8b15-e8e6f3dc9897",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9b07d017-a5af-4866-b08a-03627cad04dd"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "bcf53f09-19ec-4be5-85d2-d784a795a66d",
      "position": 11,
      "properties": {
        "description": "You made a lot of progress on your project today! Let's take a moment to reflect on what you have accomplished so far and what you need to focus on next.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Wrap Up",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "bcf53f09-19ec-4be5-85d2-d784a795a66d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9b07d017-a5af-4866-b08a-03627cad04dd"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "8b88c227-5203-466f-bad8-ca317441e35a",
      "position": 12,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to respond to the Day 1 Reflection prompt on the Natural Language Processing Project Planning Guide.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time permits, have students share their thoughts and ideas with a neighbor."
          },
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "You can use the Day 1 Reflection as an optional completion assessment."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "8b88c227-5203-466f-bad8-ca317441e35a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9b07d017-a5af-4866-b08a-03627cad04dd"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d00d65b8-a343-4b92-9813-494af7abdf2c",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Like in the examples we have seen in this unit, you are using computer science to analyze, manipulate, and generate text using natural language processing techniques. You are also using your software engineering characteristics to create your programs.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Warm Up",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d00d65b8-a343-4b92-9813-494af7abdf2c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "55e5f698-887c-4814-8d1e-6683aef0ba50"
      }
    },
