    {
      "key": "2936ba55-0881-495e-af01-5ecb7538fe49",
      "position": 13,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Natural Language Processing Project Planning Guide:** Use the rubric in the Natural Language Processing Project Planning Guide to assess the projects.",
        "name": "Assessment: Grading the Project"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2936ba55-0881-495e-af01-5ecb7538fe49",
        "lesson_activity.key": "fc58372b-e306-4a0a-ae9f-2fc46d8a9a96"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5f78bae5-1b70-47e4-92cb-3258ebd47acf",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What strategies did you use while working on the FRQs in Units 1 and 2?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students recall using annotation strategies to identify keywords and using manipulatives and graphic organizers to plan their solutions before writing code.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What were some keywords you looked for to assist you in answering the questions?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share example keywords, such as return or parameter, to identify what a method should do or what information a method or constructor needed.",
        "name": "What Do We Know?"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5f78bae5-1b70-47e4-92cb-3258ebd47acf",
        "lesson_activity.key": "db7141eb-9cb0-439b-8974-ecd7e5e6ddd5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7b241f62-7177-4ed7-95d5-6b97e6b5634d",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "During previous FRQ days, we worked with our peers through the FRQ process. Today, you will still have an opportunity to collaborate with your peers, but you will work through most of the FRQ process on your own.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "FRQ Social",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7b241f62-7177-4ed7-95d5-6b97e6b5634d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9a79c1a5-2b57-4d68-9a97-41644fd690b5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "743affa3-c788-483f-8f31-9733d8edd811",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of the TicketTracker FRQ and several markers or colored pencils.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to annotate the TicketTracker FRQ using the annotation guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What questions do you have about approaching this FRQ?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share any misunderstandings or points of confusion they have about the FRQ.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Some questions students may ask include:\n* How do I start the problem?\n* What methods do I need to write?\n* Is there an example I can review?\n* How will this FRQ be graded?"
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "743affa3-c788-483f-8f31-9733d8edd811",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9a79c1a5-2b57-4d68-9a97-41644fd690b5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ea79aa83-577d-46a7-9e3c-bff2cb1eb115",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Do This:** Explain the steps for the activity:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Input, Process, Output\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Writing\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Scoring\n\n**Group:** Place students in groups of 3-4.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of the TicketTracker FRQ Graphic Organizer.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to complete the TicketTracker FRQ Graphic Organizer."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ea79aa83-577d-46a7-9e3c-bff2cb1eb115",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9a79c1a5-2b57-4d68-9a97-41644fd690b5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "20afbdd4-c504-43b4-b1f0-83b6b364004f",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to return to their seats and complete the TicketTracker FRQ.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "FRQ Writing",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "As students work, you may use a timer to help students pace themselves. If students finish early, you can suggest that they:\n\n* Trace their code to ensure it's correct.\n* Check their graphic organizer to ensure they used all notes to write their solution.\n\nDifferentiation Suggestions:\n* Students who need more time should complete the constructor and choose one of the methods to write.\n* Students who are unsure of where to start should begin writing pseudocode for their solution."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "20afbdd4-c504-43b4-b1f0-83b6b364004f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9a79c1a5-2b57-4d68-9a97-41644fd690b5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a9577c9d-80f7-4036-8674-79d800f0f599",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Group:** Place students in pairs.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of the TicketTracker FRQ Scoring Guidelines.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students assess their solution using the TicketTracker FRQ Scoring Guidelines with their partners and complete the reflection on the last page.\n\n**Do This:** Explain the potential solution and scoring guidelines:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `getFree()` loops through all elements of `tickets`\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `getFree()` checks whether an element is `0.00`\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `getFree()` counts the number of free tickets\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `getFree()` returns the count of free tickets\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `averagePrice()` loops through all elements of `tickets`\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `averagePrice()` calculates the sum of the elements\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `averagePrice()` uses `getFree()` to calculate the number of paid tickets\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `averagePrice()` calculates the average of all paid tickets\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `averagePrice()` returns the average of all paid tickets",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "FRQ Scoring",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Have students share their implementations for each component before showing the possible solution."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a9577c9d-80f7-4036-8674-79d800f0f599",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9a79c1a5-2b57-4d68-9a97-41644fd690b5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7bc14bc2-0b92-4a52-a24c-094ed1ef3007",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What is your impression of this FRQ?*\n* *What knowledge and skills did you use that you learned in this unit?*\n* *What were you confident about? What would you like to practice?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share their impressions of this FRQ and connect the concepts they learned in the unit to those assessed. Students share what they were confident about and any areas they need additional practice.",
        "name": "Closing the Loop"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7bc14bc2-0b92-4a52-a24c-094ed1ef3007",
        "lesson_activity.key": "abf01097-5544-43ce-97ec-7e75111983cf"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "562b8118-e7d9-425a-a626-3b929dae6277",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "---"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "562b8118-e7d9-425a-a626-3b929dae6277",
        "lesson_activity.key": "abf01097-5544-43ce-97ec-7e75111983cf"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a9dfb8d1-d2c1-49ae-a8c1-796744aa79b0",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**TicketTracker FRQ:** The TicketTracker FRQ handout can be used as an optional formative assessment.",
        "name": "Assessment (Optional)"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a9dfb8d1-d2c1-49ae-a8c1-796744aa79b0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "abf01097-5544-43ce-97ec-7e75111983cf"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f113eba4-d371-4dc4-abb9-c0a31d889d48",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Today, you will complete a free response question called BingoCaller almost completely on your own. To approach this problem, let’s start by using our annotation strategies.",
        "name": "Annotate",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f113eba4-d371-4dc4-abb9-c0a31d889d48",
        "lesson_activity.key": "822b54c5-6b88-42be-97a7-6f017c3bd7e8"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "fd64586a-5b66-439d-9abf-4ca65962df02",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to review the annotation strategies.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of the BingoCaller FRQ handout and a sheet of scratch paper.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to individually annotate the FRQ. \n\n**Group:** Place students in groups of two.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students compare their annotations with their partners.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What questions do you have about approaching this free response question?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share any misunderstandings or points of confusion they have about the FRQ.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Point out words in the directions or starter code when addressing student questions."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "fd64586a-5b66-439d-9abf-4ca65962df02",
        "lesson_activity.key": "822b54c5-6b88-42be-97a7-6f017c3bd7e8"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f46d1c96-2cd5-45d1-9ca7-a8ab4e64fe5c",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Before writing your solution in Java, let’s plan it using pseudocode. Writing your algorithm out in pseudocode helps you plan your algorithm without worrying about the syntax rules of the programming language.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Pseudocode",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f46d1c96-2cd5-45d1-9ca7-a8ab4e64fe5c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4b0de98f-9905-441c-b662-9e1dd688bb6d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "51456833-98a2-4c49-b198-d36dfce6ff10",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to plan their solutions for parts A and B using pseudocode on their scratch paper.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "After five minutes, you can suggest that students move on to the second half of the FRQ."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "51456833-98a2-4c49-b198-d36dfce6ff10",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4b0de98f-9905-441c-b662-9e1dd688bb6d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c14ca28a-a36c-4326-887b-e541048bc4e1",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "The last step is to write your solution in Java. Using your pseudocode, write your solution to the FRQ. You will have 10 minutes to complete this task.",
        "name": "Implement",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c14ca28a-a36c-4326-887b-e541048bc4e1",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4b0de98f-9905-441c-b662-9e1dd688bb6d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "df574f8c-d6e4-45b9-abd5-f79c300880f8",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to convert their pseudocode into Java on the BingoCaller FRQ handout.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If students finish early, suggest:\n* Trace their code to ensure it is correct.\n* Check their solution to ensure it aligns with their pseudocode solution."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "df574f8c-d6e4-45b9-abd5-f79c300880f8",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4b0de98f-9905-441c-b662-9e1dd688bb6d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "03858356-c350-4682-a450-f68430d602d1",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of the BingoCaller FRQ Scoring Guidelines.\n\n**Group:** Place students in groups of two.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Ask students to assess their work with their partners using the BingoCaller FRQ Scoring Guidelines.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Scoring and Review"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "03858356-c350-4682-a450-f68430d602d1",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4b0de98f-9905-441c-b662-9e1dd688bb6d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f8fed80e-b64b-4a52-8ea3-55b92e75fdb5",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Congratulations on completing another FRQ! As with any problem we solve in Java, there are multiple approaches to solving an FRQ. Let’s explore some approaches to today’s FRQ.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f8fed80e-b64b-4a52-8ea3-55b92e75fdb5",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4b0de98f-9905-441c-b662-9e1dd688bb6d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "374395a6-f6e2-452d-bf9b-b2792ceba024",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Do This:** Explain the potential solution and scoring guidelines:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `hasBeenCalled()` returns `false` if the given number is invalid (less than `0` or greater than `75`)\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `hasBeenCalled()` returns the correct entry in `numbersCalled` (no bounds error)\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `getRandomNumber()` generates a random integer within the correct range based on the parameter `letter`\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `getRandomNumber()` returns an `int` value\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `makeCall()` selects a random letter from `COLUMN_LETTERS`\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `makeCall()` uses `getRandomNumber()` to get a random number based on the random letter chosen\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `makeCall()` uses `hasBeenCalled()` to check whether the bingo call has been previously made\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `makeCall()` returns a `String` containing the correct result based on whether the bingo call has been previously made\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> `makeCall()` marks the corresponding bingo call as `true` in `numbersCalled`"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "374395a6-f6e2-452d-bf9b-b2792ceba024",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4b0de98f-9905-441c-b662-9e1dd688bb6d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b84c4bfc-b697-4f4a-93de-55000c666cbb",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Distribute:** Give each student one sticky note or scrap piece of paper.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students respond to the prompt on their sticky note or scrap piece of paper.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Play the music clip to cue the Give One, Get One activity and direct students to participate in a Give One, Get One.",
        "name": "Give One, Get One"
      },
