    {
      "key": "1ae12250-aa3d-42dc-85db-84d75f9f7b9f",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of the GrayscaleImage FRQ handout and Java Quick Reference.",
        "duration": "25",
        "name": "Writing",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "This is the first time students have used the Java Quick Reference. While students may or may not need it for this FRQ, students should practice using it to become more familiar with this resource before the exam."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "1ae12250-aa3d-42dc-85db-84d75f9f7b9f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "298c1f2c-965d-4d5a-b2a9-60a791feff6a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d0568bbd-b435-4932-a320-0aabeed9a115",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "When you take the AP CSA Exam, you will receive a copy of the Java Quick Reference, which lists methods from the Java library that the exam may include. There are likely things on this reference that are unfamiliar to you at the moment, and you may or may not need to reference it as you work on this FRQ. It is helpful to be familiar with this resource for the exam.\n\nYou now have 25 minutes to develop your response to the Free Response Question. Remember to use the strategies we have practiced!",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d0568bbd-b435-4932-a320-0aabeed9a115",
        "lesson_activity.key": "298c1f2c-965d-4d5a-b2a9-60a791feff6a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "6217adf7-856c-4e91-bca0-e4ea80f26588",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students complete the Free Response Question.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Since this is the first independent Free Response Question, students may need guidance in managing their time. Periodically remind students how much time remains and what part they should work on. Students should spend about 12-13 minutes on each part. For each part, students should spend 2-3 minutes annotating, 5 minutes writing pseudocode, and 5 minutes writing their solution in Java."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "6217adf7-856c-4e91-bca0-e4ea80f26588",
        "lesson_activity.key": "298c1f2c-965d-4d5a-b2a9-60a791feff6a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "6d104589-efa4-4846-9f82-ec696daa084d",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of the GrayscaleImage FRQ Scoring Guidelines.\n\n**Group:** Place students in pairs.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students compare their solutions with their partners and assess their work using the GrayscaleImage FRQ Scoring Guidelines.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Scoring and Review"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "6d104589-efa4-4846-9f82-ec696daa084d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "298c1f2c-965d-4d5a-b2a9-60a791feff6a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3cc259a2-dd6e-467e-96fe-7c11cce37e64",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Congratulations on completing another FRQ! As with any problems we solve in Java, there are multiple approaches to solving an FRQ. Let's look at one solution to today's FRQ.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3cc259a2-dd6e-467e-96fe-7c11cce37e64",
        "lesson_activity.key": "298c1f2c-965d-4d5a-b2a9-60a791feff6a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "83ca6f05-2faf-458c-bdef-8b46bce76fc3",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Do This:** Explain the potential solution and scoring guidelines:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  `countBlackPixels()` access all entries in `pixels`\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  `countBlackPixels()` compares an element in the array with `BLACK` or with `0` during traversal\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  `countBlackPixels()` initializes and increments a counter\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  `countBlackPixels()` returns the correct count of the number of black pixels in `pixels`\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  `lightenImage()` accesses all necessary elements in at least one row or one column of `pixels`\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  `lightenImage()` accesses all entries in `pixels`\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  `lightenImage()` increases the value at index `[row][col]` by the value found at index `[row + 2][col + 2]`\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  `lightenImage()` modifies all appropriate elements of `pixels`\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  `lightenImage()`assigns `WHITE` or `255` to elements of `pixels` that would otherwise have a value greater than `WHITE`"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "83ca6f05-2faf-458c-bdef-8b46bce76fc3",
        "lesson_activity.key": "298c1f2c-965d-4d5a-b2a9-60a791feff6a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e04577b0-efd4-4513-9a67-a12c41f470ca",
