    {
      "key": "46853181-9cfe-4b0f-9dcf-df75a503dbe1",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We have seen some examples of image filters, collages, and animations throughout the unit. People often use images and image filters are often used in collages and animations to portray a story about personal experiences or interests.",
        "name": "Personal Narratives",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "46853181-9cfe-4b0f-9dcf-df75a503dbe1",
        "lesson_activity.key": "91f41f2b-1a9c-48c8-bfc3-ce4674912ebc"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e5f5bbe6-bc62-44ba-8069-80a708b7f957",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Show examples of different types of personal narratives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What does this make you wonder about how you could create a collage or animation about your personal experiences or interests?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share ideas about collages or animations they might make to portray their personal experiences or interests. Students might wonder about how more complex visuals might be created or about the design choices the creators made about their visuals.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of the Personal Narrative Project Planning Guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the project requirements.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to read the rubric on pages 2 and 3.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What do you notice about the project requirements and rubric? What does success look like for this project?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share what they notice about the project requirements and rubric and identify the components to implement in their program.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What barriers do you anticipate to achieving success on this project?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students identify barriers they anticipate and share any questions they have about the project.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Hold That Thought strategy to allow students to write down their thoughts on paper first. Emphasize that they do not need to write complete sentences – they can write a few words, bullet points, draw a quick sketch, or anything else that will help them gather and recall their thoughts when it is time to share with the class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e5f5bbe6-bc62-44ba-8069-80a708b7f957",
        "lesson_activity.key": "91f41f2b-1a9c-48c8-bfc3-ce4674912ebc"
      }
    },
