    {
      "key": "a973f2c0-ea08-45fe-8b83-206b04f62ec8",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We have seen some examples of programs that use natural language processing techniques throughout the unit. Programs and devices often use natural language processing to interact with a user to answer questions, find information, or execute commands.",
        "name": "Natural Language Processing",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a973f2c0-ea08-45fe-8b83-206b04f62ec8",
        "lesson_activity.key": "b8d60920-0812-42ba-8baa-cfe310b14cf2"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e51a1b3c-b9ff-4bf2-a244-df2307f0e3a4",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Show examples of different types of programs and devices that use natural language processing.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What does this make you wonder about how you could create a program that uses natural language processing to analyze, manipulate, or generate text?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share ideas about programs they might make using natural language processing, such as chatbots, story generators, or social media analyzers.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of the Natural Language Processing Project Planning Guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the project requirements.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to read the rubric on pages 2 and 3.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What do you notice about the project requirements and rubric? What does success look like for this project?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share what they notice about the project requirements and rubric and identify the components to implement in their program.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What barriers do you anticipate to achieving success on this project?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students identify barriers they anticipate and share any questions they have about the project.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Hold That Thought strategy to allow students to write down their thoughts on paper first. Emphasize that they do not need to write complete sentences – they can write a few words, bullet points, draw a quick sketch, or anything else that will help them gather and recall their thoughts when it is time to share with the class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e51a1b3c-b9ff-4bf2-a244-df2307f0e3a4",
        "lesson_activity.key": "b8d60920-0812-42ba-8baa-cfe310b14cf2"
      }
    },
